title: Grateful Dead Live at Rich Stadium on 1989-07-04
lineage: mac > Nakamichi BX-125E > Emu 0202 > Wavelab 5 > wav 24/96 Wavelab 5 (with iZotope Ozone 4) > iZotope RX Advanced > wav 16/44.1 > CD Wave > TLH > flac16; from OTS
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Greatest Story Ever Told, Cold Rain & Snow, Walkin' Blues, Row Jimmy, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Stagger Lee, Looks Like Rain, Deal

Set 2

Touch Of Gray, Women Are Smarter, Ship of Fools-> Playin' In The Band Reprise-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam-> I Will Take You Home-> All Along The Watchtower-> Morning Dew-> Not Fade Away, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Best aud of this show on the archive This was a fun show, for the band as well as the crowd. You can hear it. A real strong Bertha/Greatest Story to open, and they never let up (smokin' Deal to close the first set). I'll give it four stars because there's a mistake here and there and Jerry's voice is froggier than usual (even for the late 80's), but this is definitely deserving of repeated listening/download. A great show.
best audio indeed thank you. great show.
